  "prompt": "Where can you buy Lego blocks all in the same color?",
  "response": "Buying Lego blocks in a single color can be done through various channels:\n\n1. **Lego's Official Website (Pick a Brick)**: Lego's official website has a \"Pick a Brick\" section where you can select specific bricks and colors. This is a straightforward way to get precisely what you need.\n\n2. **BrickLink**: This is a popular marketplace for buying and selling Lego pieces. You can search for specific colors and types of bricks, and purchase from a wide range of sellers.\n\n3. **eBay**: Often, collectors and sellers offer bulk Lego lots sorted by color. Make sure to read descriptions and reviews carefully to ensure you\u2019re getting what you need.\n\n4. **Local Toy Stores or Specialized Stores**: Some physical stores specializing in Lego or toys may offer bulk or specialized Lego selections where you can find bricks sorted by color.\n\n5. **Amazon**: Amazon offers various Lego sets and collections, including bulk bricks that may be sorted by color. Check product details to ensure color consistency.\n\n6. **Community Groups and Swap Meet**: Local Lego user groups or online communities may sometimes offer buying, selling, or trading sessions.\n\nRemember to check the seller's reputation and reviews to ensure you're getting genuine Lego products.",
